shedCommunist Party activists such as Claudia Jones,artists and writers such as Beulah Richardson, and lesser knownorganizers such as Vicki Garvin and Thelma Dale.These women were part of a black left that laid much ofthe groundwork for both the Civil Rights Movement of the1960s and later strains of black radicalism. Radicalism atthe Crossroads offers a sustained and in-depth analysis ofthe political thought and activism of black women radicalsduring the Cold War period and adds a new dimension toour understanding of this tumultuous time in United Stateshistory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American radicalsxHistoryy20th century. 0aAfrican American women political activistsxHistoryy20th century. 0aCommunismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aFeminismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aRadicalismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen radicalszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aCold.  aCommunist.  aDale.  aDayo.  aGarvin.  aGore.  aParty.  aThelma.  aVicki.  aWar.  aactivists.  aartists.  ablack.  acommunity.  aduring.  adynamic.  aearly.  aestablished.  aexamines.  aextended.  aincluding.  alesser-known.  aorganizers.  aradical.  asuch.  aunearths.  awomen.  awriters.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814732366.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814733028423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814733028/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aE